e to, to keep the camp running smoothly. If you don't have a well balanced group of the proper level for bugs you will be training in no time and possibly losing members or getting others killed. I personally have sat in the circle room killing green MOB's for 5 hours waiting on lists for all 3 kobold spawn points and the bug group. It sucks but somedays that is the way it goes. Hopefully we will discover some nice 40+ outdoor zones in Kunark and we can thin out the crowds in LGuk and SolB. I would like to come down to LGuk soon and get me some of the much needed items I am lacking. I really don't know the zone well though and waiting on lists sucks even more if you are unfamiliar with the zone.</FONT><P>Berton Strongheart 48th Paladin<BR>Sanctuary<BR>Nameless<BR>"It's all fun and games until someone gets shot in the leg."<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#989dca><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/upaleiceblade.showPublicProfile>Pale Iceblade</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>4/18/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#333333>3:39:41 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Re: sigh</FONT></B><HR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2> Let me get this straight..you waited for 11 hours for a list!?  You need to relax a bit and find some other things to concentrate on. There is much fun to be had solo while you wait, and if you've NOT a friend in the group that you are waiting on..be sure, your chances are slim, so make other plans. <br>
